# Markdown Coding Standards (CRITICAL: STRICT ENFORCEMENT)

- MD022: MANDATORY. Every heading (#, ##, ###) MUST have EXACTLY one blank line before it and EXACTLY one blank line after it.
  - Bad: `### Heading\nContent`
  - Good: `### Heading\n\nContent`
- MD031: MANDATORY. Fenced code blocks (```) MUST be surrounded by blank lines. Always ensure there is a blank line before and after code blocks.
- MD032: MANDATORY. Lists MUST be surrounded by blank lines.
- MD030: MANDATORY. Spaces after list markers. Always ensure there is EXACTLY one space after list markers.
  - Bad: `1.  Numbered list` (two spaces)
  - Good: `1. Numbered list` (one space)
  - Bad: `-  Bullet list` (two spaces)
  - Good: `- Bullet list` (one space)
- MD038: MANDATORY. No spaces inside code spans. Code spans MUST NOT start or end with a space.
  - Bad: `` ` code ` ``
  - Good: `` `code` ``

# Project Context

- This project is a Web system for managing Amazon revenue.
- Backend: Spring Boot 3 + Java 17
- Frontend: Vue 3 + Vite + TypeScript
- Database: MySQL (Docker)
- Internationalization (i18n): Supported (Default: Japanese)

# Coding Guidelines

- Use SLF4J (@Slf4j) for logging instead of `printStackTrace()`.
- Follow the existing package structure and naming conventions.
- Ensure all messages and labels are externalized to `messages.properties` for i18n support.
- When creating documentation (MD files), always include links to the corresponding Java implementation files and related design documents.
- Documentation Directory Structure (Backend):
  - API (Grouped by Controller): `backend/docs/api/{ControllerName}/`
    - Class Detail: `class-detail.md`
    - Endpoint Detail: `api-{EndpointName}.md`
  - Application Services: `backend/docs/application/services/{FunctionalGroup}/`
  - Domain Services: `backend/docs/domain/services/{FunctionalGroup}/`
  - Repositories: `backend/docs/infrastructure/repositories/{FunctionalGroup}/`
- Documentation Directory Structure (Frontend):
  - Pages: `frontend-vue/docs/pages/`
  - Router: `frontend-vue/docs/router/`
